An Act relative to wiretapping in the Commonwealth.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Subparagraph 1 of paragraph D of section 99 of chapter 272 of the General Laws, as
2 appearing in the 2006 Official Edition, is hereby amended by adding the following clause:- g. for
3 a person not acting under color of law to intercept a wire communication containing a person's
4 speech or oral communication where such person is a party to the communication or where one
5 of the parties to the communication has given prior consent to such interception.
